# English Version

## Current Status

Sinnet.top is currently a **Single Page Application (SPA)**. All content is stacked on a single page, which creates several challenges:

- **Poor crawl efficiency** – Search engine bots rely on distinct URLs and hyperlinks; an SPA limits indexable depth.
- **Missing critical meta tags** – No unique `<title>` or `<meta name="description">` tags were found, hurting click‑through rates and relevance signals.
- **Weak GEO foundation** – Generative AI models prefer well‑structured, linkable content. The SPA format makes it harder for LLMs to extract and cite information reliably.

## SEO Recommendations

### 1. Restructure as a Multi‑Page Website
Create a clear information architecture with separate pages:

| Page | URL example | Purpose |
|------|-------------|---------|
| Home | `/` | Brand value, key offerings |
| AI App | `/ai-app` | Detailed intro to the AI tennis coach |
| Shop | `/shop` | Products (shoes, balls, etc.) + PDPs |
| About | `/about` | Team, mission, story |

### 2. Add Unique Meta Tags
For every page, define a unique `<title>` (50–60 chars) and `<meta name="description">` (150–160 chars) that naturally include primary keywords.

**Example for Homepage:**
```html
<title>Sinnet – AI Tennis Coach & Affordable Gear</title>
<meta name="description" content="Sinnet provides an AI virtual coach app and factory‑direct tennis equipment. Break down high coaching fees and brand markups.">
